gh reactivity, requiring high outgassing for detectability. We calculate\nthat 10s of hours of JWST time are required for a potential detection of\nPH$_3$. Yet because PH$_3$ is spectrally active in the same wavelength regions\nas other atmospherically important molecules (e.g., H$_2$O and CH$_4$),\nsearches for PH$_3$ can be carried out at no additional observational cost to\nsearches for other molecules relevant to exoplanet habitability.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 11 Oct 2019 14:48:57 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 28 Oct 2019 18:54:19 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-02-12"}
